First attested in the ''{{w|Wamyō Ruijushō}}'' (938 {{CE}}), as ''man'yōgana'' form {{m|ja||於保无|tr=opomu- → ōmu-}} within {{m|ja|大御宝|於保无太加良|tr=opomutakara → ōmutakara|[[people]]|pos=as a ''kun'' reading of {{ja-l|人民}}}}.

Shift from {{inh|ja|ojp|大御|tr={{IPAfont|⟨opomi<sub>1</sub>⟩}} → ōmi-|pos=[[prefix]] of [[maximum]] [[honorific]]}}.

Both ''ōmu-'' and ''ōn-'' readings likely existed in free variation until the development of the {{ja-r|ん}} morpheme.

