{{also|w:Honorific speech in Japanese#Honorific prefixes}}
Prefixed to the Sino-Japanese words, as in {{m|ja|御主人|tr=goshujin||[[husband]]}}.

While in general this prefix is optional, in many cases it is so commonly used that the base word can no longer be used in isolation, as in {{m|ja|御飯|tr=gohan|| rice}} – the form ×{{m|ja||飯|tr=*han}} is not used alone, though it can be used as parts of compounds (such as {{ja-l|炊飯}}, ''suihan'', “[[rice]] [[cook]]ing”), and the character can be read in isolation as ''meshi''.

